com.sun.enterprise.security.jauth

Interface DependentCallbackHandler


  • public interface DependentCallbackHandler
    A marker interface that may be implemented by a CallBackHandler.

    When a CallbackHandler that implements this interface, is passed as an argument to the getServerAuthContext or getClientAuthContext methods of the AuthConfig class, the AuthConfig system will wrap the handler in a special internal CallbackHandler that will delegate any unsupported Callbacks to the default CallbackHandler of the AuthConfig system. The modules of the context will receive this wrapping handler at initialization, and the effect will be to allow systems to extend or override the callbacks handled by the default handler of the config system with those handled by the wrapped handler.

    Version:
    %I%, %G%
